txt-patron2-1: On behalf of myself and the entire freesewing community, I would like to express my gratitude and appreciation that you have made this generous commitment. TODO
txt-patron2-2: First and foremost, we are going to continue doing what we do. I think it is fair to assume that as our Patron, this is what you expect from us. If that makes you feel like you have made no difference, let me assure you: That is not the case. TODO
txt-patron2-3: Your commitment as a Patron is a great motivator for us. It tells us that what we do is worthwhile, and it is helps us secure a sustainable future for freesewing.org, our code, our patterns, and our community. TODO
txt-patron2-4: It is this, somewhat nebulous, dimension to your patronage which matters most. Becoming a Patron of Freesewing was an act of kindness and generosity on your behalf for which we can only offer our gratitude. We coudn't possibly repay you. TODO
txt-patron2-ps: PS: If you are on Twitter, Instagram, or GitHub, please let me know so we can follow you from the official freesewing acccount. It's a patron's priviledge üôÇ TODO

txt-patron4-2: I'll be sending your gift in the mail soon, but before doing so I'll reach out to you to double-check your shipping address. TODO
txt-patron4-3: Meanwhile, I've already added you to our list of patrons on freesewing.org. TODO
